Gluten-Free High-Altitude Carrot Cake

As if baking at 8,600 feet wasn’t a tough enough challenge, this cake also needed to be gluten-free. This recipe is based on this recipe:

https://delishably.com/desserts/High-Altitude-Cooking-Carrot-Cake

With a few changes. I replaced wheat flour with this corn-and-yuca flour:

I increased the eggs from 4 to 5, and reduced the sugar from 1.5 cups to 1 cup.
